sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS(edge)
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Jupyter as JupyterLab Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP
    participant DSP as Data Science Pipelines API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Tekton as Tekton Backend<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Runtime as Runtime Image Pod
    participant K8sAPI as OpenShift API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant DB as Database Servers<br/>(MongoDB/PostgreSQL/MSSQL)
    participant PyPI as PyPI Registry<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User, Jupyter: Flow 1: User Accesses Notebook Workbench (RHOAI 2.x)

    User->>Router: GET /notebook/{ns}/{user}/*<br/>HTTPS/443
    Router->>OAuth: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS
    Note right of OAuth: Validates OAuth cookie<br/>Redirects to OpenShift OAuth if unauthenticated
    OAuth->>Jupyter: Proxy to notebook<br/>HTTP/8888 plaintext (localhost)<br/>Trusted after OAuth
    Jupyter-->>OAuth: JupyterLab UI / API response
    OAuth-->>Router: Response
    Router-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over Jupyter, Runtime: Flow 2: Elyra Pipeline Submission

    Jupyter->>DSP: POST pipeline submission<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: SA token + SSL cert
    DSP->>Tekton: Create pipeline run<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: SA token
    Tekton->>Runtime: Launch runtime pod<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount
    Runtime-->>Tekton: Pipeline step complete
    Tekton-->>DSP: Pipeline status
    DSP-->>Jupyter: Pipeline result

    Note over Jupyter, PyPI: Flow 3: Notebook Egress (User-initiated)

    Jupyter->>K8sAPI: oc CLI commands<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Jupyter: API response

    Jupyter->>DB: Database queries<br/>MongoDB:27017, PostgreSQL:5432, MSSQL:1433<br/>Auth: User credentials
    DB-->>Jupyter: Query results

    Jupyter->>PyPI: pip install packages<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    PyPI-->>Jupyter: Python packages
